    "brand_story_combo_main": {
      "type": "brand-story-combo",
      "name": "Story Layout Bundle",
      "settings": {
        "width": "wrapper",
        "top_heading": "<p>“Italy is the best, most wonderful theater in the world — an open-air theater where everybody can decide what role to play.”</p>",
        "top_text": "",
        "top_image": "shopify://shop_images/roberto-coin-the-explorer-of-beauty-cropped-face-upscale-2.4x.jpg",
        "caption_text": "Roberto stands by Castelvecchio, a fortress built by Verona’s Scaliger dynasty in the 14th century.",
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
    "blog_two_col_intro": {
      "type": "section-two-column-text",
      "name": "Two Column Text",
      "settings": {
        "width": "wrapper",
        "max_width": 1100,
        "gap": 120,
        "left_heading": "",
        "left_text": "<p>Roberto Coin has traveled the world in search of beautiful inspirations for the jewelry that bears his name. “I find beauty everywhere,” he says, “in nature, in people, in architecture, in art and in food.” And his collections bear that out: since starting the brand in 1996, he’s taken inspiration from a wide variety of sources, from the natural world in Animalier, to the stars, with his Zodiac Medallions.</p><p>Still, few places inspire Coin like his native Italy. When you’re walking through Verona—or any Italian city—with Roberto Coin, you can’t expect to get anywhere fast. Every couple steps he stops to point out another beautiful thing—the design of the rosoni medallions on a building’s facade, or the red brick merlons of Castelvecchio.</p>",
        "left_text_style": "body",
        "left_italic": true,
        "right_heading": "",
        "right_text": "<p>Now he’s paused to admire the Ponte Pietra, a Roman bridge completed around 100 BC and still in use today. “Even when I’m by myself, I am never alone,” says Roberto. “Walking through this city is like watching a film for me, I can go back in my mind and see what it used to be in those days.”</p><p>Today, he’s in Italy’s città dell’amore, Verona, where he spoke about his process, his philosophy of life, and the origins of his new “Love in Verona” collection.</p>",
        "right_text_style": "body",
        "right_italic": true,
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
