        "center_text": "<p><strong>YOU’VE TRAVELED THE WORLD — AND YET YOU KEEP RETURNING TO YOUR HOME, ITALY. WHAT MAKES IT DIFFERENT FROM OTHER PLACES?</strong></p><p>For me Italy is the best, most wonderful theater in the world — an open-air theater where everybody can decide what role to play. And I have decided to play the Explorer of Beauty.</p><p>As Italians, beauty is in our DNA. We have the good fortune to be born in a place where we are surrounded by art. Maybe we get used to the beauty immediately and then we can’t live without it.</p>",
